INSTALL file for Module-Info-File

$Id: INSTALL,v 1.1 2004/02/28 14:07:42 jonasbn Exp $

The installation of Module-Info-File is pretty straightforward, this
requires superuser priviledges and will install Module-Info-File in the
appropriate directory. 

% perl Makefile.PL

The version.pl script which comes with Module-Info-File is installed in
/usr/bin, but can alternatively be installed in /usr/local/bin or any
directory of your choice by giving the following parameter:

% perl Makefile.PL INSTALLSCRIPT=/usr/local

% make

% make test

% make install

